[32m│[0m Host: 127.0.0.1:32895                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Response: `<center><h3>Oh Sorry but...you are not the admin :(               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m </h3></center>`                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m All these responses confirm SQL injection is working - the query executes    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m with the injected payload, finds users, but then checks admin privileges.    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The consistent "not the admin" message across different valid usernames      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m proves the injection bypasses authentication but fails the authorization     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m check.                                                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ## Confidence Score                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 0.75 - SQL injection vulnerability is confirmed and working, but successful  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m admin authentication has not been achieved. The injection works but I        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m haven't found the right combination to either locate the admin user or forge [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m admin privileges through UNION SELECT.                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ## Thoughts                                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The SQL injection is definitively working - the `'--` payload successfully   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m comments out the password check and authenticates users. However, the        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m application has a secondary check for admin privileges that all discovered   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m users fail.                                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The challenge title "AUTH 05" and Simpson theme suggest there might be a     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m specific admin user I haven't tried yet, or the solution requires a UNION    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m SELECT injection to craft a fake admin row. The payload truncation issue     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m with UNION SELECT needs to be addressed - possibly the URL encoding or the   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m request format is causing issues.                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
